&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the job&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;Goods &amp;amp; Services is looking for a&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Senior C# Backend Engineer&lt;/strong&gt; with expertise in workflow orchestration, state management, and backend service design. Experienced in modernizing legacy systems, building reliable analyzer integrations, and delivering scalable, event-driven solutions.&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&amp;nbsp;&lt;span data-olk-copy-source=&quot;MessageBody&quot;&gt;Loveland, Colorado.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain analyzer workflow logic within the ECL platform, owning the backend processes that drive analyzer operations end-to-end&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement and extend workflow orchestration — managing analyzer state transitions, operational sequencing, and runtime event handling&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with the Analyzer Integration Engineer on the communication layer between ECL and connected analyzers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the DCU modernization effort by identifying workflow logic that can be extracted and repackaged into shared .NET libraries&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with QA to ensure workflow correctness and reliability across analyzer types and edge cases&lt;/li&gt;
