&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of professional C# / .NET backend development experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience building workflow or orchestration systems — state machines, process sequencing, or similar patterns&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solid understanding of backend service design and inter-service communication&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work within and around legacy codebases without breaking production.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborative approach to working alongside integration and infrastructure engineers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nice to have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exposure to medical device, laboratory, or instrument integration workflows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with .NET Framework 4.x and modern .NET migration patterns&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with Azure Service Bus or event-driven messaging&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Background picking up ownership of an inherited or underdocumented system&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Goods &amp;amp; Services&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;Goods &amp;amp; Services is a product design and engineering company.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
