&lt;p&gt;Headquartered in the &lt;strong&gt;United States&lt;/strong&gt;, we operate regional development centers in &lt;strong&gt;Mexico &lt;/strong&gt;and the &lt;strong&gt;United Kingdom&lt;/strong&gt;. This global footprint—anchored by our &lt;strong&gt;nearshore &lt;/strong&gt;model—enables us to deliver at scale with the speed, efficiency, and cultural alignment our clients expect.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the job&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;Goods &amp;amp; Services is looking for a &lt;strong&gt;Staff SDET&lt;/strong&gt; to design, develop, and maintain automated testing solutions for native mobile applications and responsive web platforms. The ideal candidate combines strong software development skills with quality engineering expertise and leverages AI tools to accelerate test design, automation development, and defect analysis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, develop, and maintain automation frameworks for iOS Native Applications, Android Native Applications, and Responsive Web Applications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop automated smoke, regression, integration, and end-to-end test suites.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create reusable automation components and libraries.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure automation reliability, maintainability, and scalability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Validate mobile-specific functionality, including Push notifications, Deep links, Device permissions, Biometric authentication, Offline functionality, Application lifecycle behavior, Cross-device compatibility,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Execute functional, integration, regression, and exploratory testing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and execute API automation tests.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Validate integrations between mobile applications and backend services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure data integrity and system reliability across environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Integrate automated testing into CI/CD pipelines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support release readiness activities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor automation execution and quality metrics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and address automation failures and flaky tests.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use AI tools to accelerate Test case generation, Automation development, Defect investigation, Test data creation, Log analysis, and Documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Validate and refine AI-generated outputs before implementation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continuously identify opportunities to improve testing efficiency through AI-assisted workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll need:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years of experience in QA Automation or SDET roles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience testing native iOS and Android applications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience testing responsive web applications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong programming skills in JavaScript, TypeScript, Java, Python, C#, or Kotlin.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with automation tools such as Appium, Playwright, Selenium, XCUITest, Espresso&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with API testing tools such as Postman, Karate DSL, REST Assured.&lt;/li&gt;
